snippet: LEAD: A California condor chick, the product of the first captive mating by the nearly extinct species, pecked at its shell for a second day today and progressed toward an expected hatching Friday or early Saturday, officials said....
lead_paragraph: LEAD: A California condor chick, the product of the first captive mating by the nearly extinct species, pecked at its shell for a second day today and progressed toward an expected hatching Friday or early Saturday, officials said.

headline.main: Condor Chick Is Progressing, With Hatching Possible Today
